Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 8
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the HTRA2 gene on chromosome 2p13.

Name: obsolete neoplastic disease
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in an abnormal mass of tissue.

Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the TIMM50 gene on chromosome 19q13.

Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the DNAJC19 gene on chromosome 3q26.

Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria with deafness
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the SERAC1 gene on chromosome 6q25.

Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 1
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the AUH gene on chromosome 9q22.

Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria with cataracts
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the CLPB gene on chromosome 11q13.

Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 3
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that has_material_basis_in mutation in the OPA3 gene.

Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria type 4
Definition: A 3-methylglutaconic aciduria that is characterized by mild or intermittent urinary excretion of 3-methylglutaconic acid.
